verbose_text: Proton transport number studies on similar perovskites demonstrated pure proton conduction up to 700degreesC under wet conditions XREF_BIBR XREF_BIBR and we believe the same for the investigated perovskite I. Further, the small amount of Ce 4+ / Ce 3+ conversion observed under TGA has not induced significant electronic conductivity as otherwise the OCP would have reduced due to electronic short circuiting.
